@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Identity
@using LabProject.Areas.Identity.Data

@inject SignInManager<ApplicationUser> SignInManager

@{
    //ViewData["Title"] = "About Us";
    Layout = SignInManager.IsSignedIn(User) ? "_Layout_Dashboard" : "_Layout";
}

<section id="about-us" class="py-5 bg-light">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="mb-4">
            <h2 class="text-center section-title">About Us</h2>
            <p class="">At Moneymind, we believe that personal finance should be simple, engaging, and tailored to your lifestyle. Our mission is to provide individuals with a comprehensive yet easy-to-use tool to track and optimize their budgets, helping them take control of their financial future.</p>
            <p class="">Founded by a team of financial enthusiasts and tech experts, Moneymind was born out of the need for a personal budgeting solution that was both practical and effective. Whether you’re a student managing your first budget, a professional saving for retirement, or a family planning for a big purchase, we have designed Moneymind to fit your needs.</p>
            <p class="">Our app helps users track income, expenses, and set up personalized savings goals. With real-time updates, notifications, and detailed reports, Moneymind gives you all the tools you need to stay on top of your finances.</p>
            <p class="">We are passionate about improving financial literacy and empowering individuals to make smarter decisions with their money. Our commitment is to build a product that grows with you, adapting to your financial goals and habits.</p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="mb-4">Our Team</h3>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-12 mb-4">
                <div class="team-member">
                    <strong>Piotr Matla</strong>
                    <p>Piotr is the driving force behind Moneymind, shaping the vision for the future of personal finance management. He is passionate about creating tools that make managing money easier for everyone.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-12 mb-4">
                <div class="team-member">
                    <strong>Klaudia Marszałek</strong>
                    <p>Klaudia brings a wealth of knowledge in software development and engineering, overseeing the technical side of Moneymind.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <h3 class="mb-4">Our Study Case</h3>
        <p class="">Developing Moneymind presented several challenges that pushed our team to rethink how we design budget management tools. One of the primary obstacles was how to make a complex system, such as personal finance tracking, feel simple and approachable without sacrificing power or flexibility.</p>
        <p class="">Early user feedback indicated that many existing apps were either too complicated for casual users or lacked the depth needed by more advanced users. Our solution was to create a flexible structure that allowed for both basic and advanced features. The result was a modular system where users could customize their experience based on their financial needs.</p>

        <h4 class="mb-4">Challenges We Overcame</h4>
        <ul class="list-unstyled">
            <li><strong>Balancing Simplicity and Power:</strong> Our initial design was either too simple, offering limited features, or too complex, confusing our users. After extensive testing, we refined the app’s interface to be both user-friendly and feature-rich, with customizable options for both beginners and experts.</li>
            <li><strong>Real-Time Updates:</strong> One of the most important features we added was real-time expense tracking. It was critical that users could see updates as soon as they made purchases. We integrated bank feeds and a smart categorization system, which automatically tagged expenses into categories like food, entertainment, and utilities.</li>
            <li><strong>Personalized Savings Goals:</strong> Our users wanted to not only track their spending but also have an easy way to save for goals such as vacations, emergency funds, and big purchases. We designed the savings feature to be motivational, showing users their progress towards goals with visual charts and reminders.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="mb-4">Results</h4>
        <p class="">Through multiple iterations and user testing, Moneymind transformed from a basic budget tracker into a powerful financial assistant that adapts to individual needs. With over 10,000 active users, we’ve received positive feedback for the app’s clean design, ease of use, and the ability to offer actionable insights into spending habits.</p>
        <p class="">We’re constantly improving Moneymind by adding new features based on user feedback, including a debt tracking module, investment portfolio integration, and enhanced reporting tools. Our goal is to continue helping users make smarter, more informed financial decisions.</p>

    </div>
</section>

